I started my mage alt because of your excellent posts about the benefits of modding/nuking.  I think mage is a nice balance between rogue and wizard in the DPS continuum (wizards have little more versatility and utility other than DPS IMO).  Mage and rogue essentially offer only DPS, so they should be competitive, even dead even, considering all kinds of encounters.<br>
<br>
I think rogues could really use a little help since all the great (and deserved) upgrades casters have gotten with focus,aa,and pop pets (charmed or summoned).  I'd like to see them competitive in DPS with a mage at about the 50 percent uptime mark, and/or given some more significant burst DPS ability than duelist.  I wish I were in better groups more often with chain-pulling/parking enchanters, but I rarely see 50 percent uptime.<br>
<br>
You can argue over where the bar should be, but obviously it's horribly wrong if monk/rogue if any caster can sustain their DPS in 100% uptime while still being able to burst for 2-3x as much for the duration of a typical PoP boss encounter or in groups with downtime, and also horribly wrong if monk/rogue sustained DPS equals the burst DPS of wizard or mage.  I'd feel slighted if I could only match a mage in a 70% uptime group.<br>
<br>
Gimme a chance to triple attack/BS and some more readily available &gt;15 dmg piercers and we'll call it even.  Unfortunately, I'm looking at spending 150k PP (the mob that drops it is permakilled on my server) for a 15/20 weapon that will actually only increase my total DPS by about 8 percent (BS dmg is about 40-45% of my total, and is independent of delay), and that's all I can get until some uber guild takes pity on me and lets me loot a +BS% or &gt;15 dmg piercer (of which there are about 4 in the game, total)<br>
<br>
However, I'm quite happy when I group with guildmates (even if they're bst/mag/necro) who outdamage me.  More exp for me =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirrudn@themagicianstower>Nirrudn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 165<br> <font color=#333333>(12/11/02 7:38:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8108.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:</span><hr size=1> What exactly is the problem with <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>casters</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> doing the most damage?  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>That's why we're casters!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  We're wielding the damn force that holds the universe together, and some guy with a dagger wants to justify doing more damage? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=archangelranari@themagicianstower>Archangel Ranari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#333333>(12/11/02 9:00:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8108.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> What exactly is the problem with casters doing the most damage? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
